31/03/2006
ROME, Italy -- Serbian Prime Minister Vojislav Kostunica discussed the status negotiation process for Kosovo on Thursday (30 March) with his Croatian and Greek counterparts, Ivo Sanader and Costas Karamanlis. 
The three prime ministers, who met at the congress of the European People's Party, agreed that the future status of Kosovo should not be imposed, but result from compromise by both sides.
Kostunica and Sanader also talked about how to improve bilateral relations between the two countries, with special emphasis on the position of the Serb minority in Croatia. 
Co-operation between the two countries was also discussed between Serbian and Greek prime ministers, especially with regard to the EU integration process. 
(Beta, Tanjug, RTS - 30/03/06)
